reflections.reflection: Last day of the year. Reflecting on how much I've grown. Still figuring things out but that's okay. Here's to another year.
New Year, new me? Let's see. Setting some intentions for this year but trying not to put too much pressure on myself.
Actually did my skincare routine tonight. Small wins count!
Applied for that promotion today. Nervous but proud of myself for going for it.
Made it to the gym today! Trying to be consistent with working out.
Grateful for the little things today. Health, roof over my head, people who care about me.
Called umma today. She's still asking when I'm going to get married. Love her but the pressure is real.
Been thinking about reconnecting with my Korean roots more. Maybe I should take language classes?
Watching all my friends get engaged. Happy for them but also feeling the pressure to figure out my love life.
Tried a new recipe today and it turned out great! Cooking is becoming therapeutic.
My apartment finally feels like home after decorating this weekend.
Got my hair done at the Korean salon. The ajumma knew exactly what I needed without explaining.
Imposter syndrome hit hard today during the team meeting. Need to remind myself that I deserve to be here.
Sometimes I feel too American for my Korean family and too Korean for my American friends. Where do I fit?
Had to decline another social invitation. Need to get better at balancing alone time with FOMO.
Anxiety was high today. Did some breathing exercises and they actually helped.
Networking event was awkward but I made some connections. Growth happens outside comfort zones.
Period cramps are killing me. Why do we have to deal with this every month?
Comparing myself to others on social media again. Need to remember everyone's journey is different.
Family dinner was nice but exhausting. The aunties kept comparing me to my cousins who are married with kids.
Brunch with the girls was exactly what I needed. Grateful for friends who get me.
Decided I'm okay being single right now. Working on myself feels more important than forcing something.
Went to that art class I signed up for. Nervous but excited to try something new.
